The paper deals with cyber attacks on power systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a security index for vulnerability assessment, which involves optimization and linear programming, indicating a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper evaluates the risk of attacks on system operation, which involves analysis and modeling, indicating a possible connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
